*.swo
*~
*.bak

# Local database
postgres-data/
apps/api/*.db
apps/api/*.db-journal

# Build / report artifacts (generated PDFs etc.)
outputs/
*.zip

# macOS Finder duplicate artifacts ("client 2.py", "page 2.tsx", "tsconfig 2.json")
# so a bulk `git add` can never commit Finder copies into the source tree.
# `* [2-9].*` catches numbered FILES with an extension; `* [2-9]/` catches
# numbered DIRECTORIES (e.g. an App Router "notificaciones 2/"); bare
# `* [2-9]` catches extensionless numbered files/dirs ("Makefile 2").
* [2-9].*
* [2-9]/
* [2-9]
* copy.*
* copy

# Local-only operator artefacts under docs/ (demo credentials, executive
# evidence bundles, ad-hoc HTML reports). Tracked docs live alongside —
# only the explicitly-named local artefacts are ignored.
docs/CREDENTIALS.md
docs/EXECUTIVE_REPORT*.html
docs/executive-evidence/

# Local session artifacts and AI tooling
CodexConvo.txt
.claude/*
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/**
# Skill installer output (reproducible from skills-lock.json + install script)
.agents/
# Symlinks created by scripts/register-design-skills.sh into .agents/
.claude/skills/design-taste-frontend
.claude/skills/gpt-taste
.claude/skills/high-end-visual-design
.claude/skills/impeccable
.claude/skills/redesign-existing-projects

# Local handoff / pasted-context notes (root-level scratch files).
# Tracked planning docs live under docs/, not at the repo root.
/CLAUDE_CODE_HANDOFF_*.md
/Checkwise-slack-feedback.txt
/*-slack-feedback.txt

# Heavy local audit-screenshot intermediates (raw recordings + silent
# masters used to produce the tracked demo.mp4). Final renders that
# ARE meant to ship stay tracked alongside.
docs/audit-screenshots/**/_raw_demo/
docs/audit-screenshots/**/demo.silent.mp4
docs/audit-screenshots/**/*.webm

# Local printables / generated PDFs (audit P4-08, 2026-05-25). The
# audit and legal packages are rendered locally for sharing; the
# definitive sources live elsewhere (audit Markdown + the legal
# document repository) so the PDFs themselves don't need version
# control. Pattern matches both the dated artifacts the audit
# flagged and any future date-stamped re-renders.
docs/audits/security/BACKEND_HARDENING_PASS_*.pdf
docs/legal/checkwise-paquete-legal-simple-v*-*.pdf
